  "prompt": "What are the penalties for money laundering under federal law?",
  "response": "Under federal law, money laundering can result in serious criminal penalties, including:\n\n1. Potential prison sentences\n- Up to 20 years in federal prison per offense\n- Potential consecutive sentences for multiple counts\n\n2. Financial penalties\n- Substantial fines, often up to $500,000 or twice the value of the property involved\n- Potential civil asset forfeiture\n\n3. Additional consequences\n- Criminal record\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Potential immigration consequences for non-citizens\n\nThe specific penalties depend on factors like the amount of money involved, specific circumstances, and whether it's a first or repeat offense. Prosecutors typically use statutes like 18 U.S. Code \u00a7 1956 and \u00a7 1957 to pursue money laundering charges.",
